ENTRY            30316   20260424   20260528   20260528       3223
SUBENT        30316001   20260424   20260528   20260528       3223
BIB                 13         27
TITLE      Cross-sections for the (n,n'), (n,p) and (n,2n)
            reactions on 107Ag and 109Ag isotopes
AUTHOR     (W.Augustyniak, M.Herman, A.Marcinkowski)
INSTITUTE  (3POLIFJ)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,247,231,1975)
           (P,INR-1464,9,1973) Short.Prelim.,uncorrected data
EXP-YEAR   (1974)
FACILITY   (VDG) 3 MeV Van de Graaff accelerator
INC-SOURCE (D-T) T(d,n) alpha reaction
           (D-D) D(d,n)He-3 reaction
DETECTOR   (GELI) 30 cm3 coaxial Ge(Li)spectrometer
METHOD     (ACTIV)
CORRECTION Data were corrected for:
           . Self-absorption of 87.7 and 93.1 keV gamma rays
             in the sample (in case of inelastic scattering)
           . Influence of low-energy neutrons from d(d,n)3He
             reaction due to deuterons accumulated in the tritium
             target during deuteron bombardment
COMMENT    Data supersedes those of entry 30262
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total uncertainties are due to:
           (ERR-1) Fluctuations of the beam current (2%)
           (ERR-2) Sample weight and composition  (1%)
           (ERR-3) Counter efficiency (6%)
           (ERR-4) Gamma-ray attenuation in the sample (7%)
HISTORY    (19751229C) OS.
           (20090115A) SD: BIB section updated
           (20260423A) VT. Entry revised
ENDBIB              27
COMMON               4          3
ERR-1      ERR-2      ERR-3      ERR-4
PER-CENT   PER-CENT   PER-CENT   PER-CENT
         2.         1.         6.         7.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           34
